

Buying Module :

- helps to manage the complete process of procuring goods and services from suppliers
- starting from identifying a need (Material Request) to completing payment for received goods (Purchase Invoice).


It ensures:
- You buy the right materials
- From the right supplier
- At the right price
- Delivered on time



üß© Importance
The Buying module is crucial because it:
- Keeps purchase costs under control
- Ensures material availability for production or sales
- Maintains supplier relationships
- Provides full purchase traceability (from request ‚Üí invoice)
- Helps with budgeting and audit compliance


üìö Key Concepts & Terminologies

| Term                            | Simple Meaning                                                    | Real Example                                    |
| ------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------- |
| **Supplier**                    | The person or company from whom you buy goods                     | Example: ‚ÄúABC Traders‚Äù supplying computer parts |
| **Material Request**            | Internal document to request materials (from warehouse or vendor) | ‚ÄúNeed 10 Laptops for new employees‚Äù             |
| **Request for Quotation (RFQ)** | Asking different suppliers for price quotes                       | Send RFQ to 3 suppliers for 10 laptops          |
| **Supplier Quotation**          | Supplier‚Äôs response with prices and terms                         | ‚ÄúABC Traders ‚Äì ‚Çπ50,000 per laptop‚Äù              |
| **Purchase Order (PO)**         | Confirmed order sent to the selected supplier                     | You finalize one supplier and place PO          |
| **Purchase Receipt (GRN)**      | Proof that items have been received                               | ‚ÄúReceived 10 laptops from ABC Traders‚Äù          |
| **Purchase Invoice (PI)**       | Supplier‚Äôs bill for payment                                       | ‚ÄúInvoice #123 from ABC Traders ‚Äì ‚Çπ5,00,000‚Äù     |
| **Payment Entry**               | Record of payment made to supplier                                | Paid ‚Çπ5,00,000 via bank transfer                |




üí°Key Theoretical Points :

:) The Buying Module integrates tightly with Stock, Accounts, and Supplier Master.
:) Every Buying transaction can affect inventory (through Purchase Receipt) and accounts (through Purchase Invoice & Payment).
:) ERPNext allows custom workflows, approval levels, and auto-updates stock values from purchase entries.


@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@

Buying Cycle :

1Ô∏è‚É£ Material Request
- This is the starting point of the buying process.
‚Üí When any department needs an item, they create this request.
  (We need to buy something.)



2Ô∏è‚É£ Request for Quotation (RFQ)
- Once you know what you need, you ask multiple suppliers for their price offers.
- The RFQ is sent to all suppliers registered in the system.
‚Üí Send this to suppliers asking for prices.
  (Ask suppliers ‚Äì ‚ÄúHow much will you charge?‚Äù)

ex: RFQ sent to 3 suppliers: HP Dealer, Dell Dealer, and Lenovo Dealer.



3Ô∏è‚É£ Supplier Quotation
- Suppliers reply with their quotation ‚Äî including price, delivery time, and terms.
- You compare the quotations and choose the best offer.
‚Üí Supplier replies with prices and terms.
  (Supplier says ‚Äì ‚ÄúMy rate is ‚Çπ___ per item.‚Äù)

ex: HP Dealer offers ‚Çπ50,000 per laptop ‚Äî best deal ‚Üí chosen supplier.


4Ô∏è‚É£ Purchase Order (PO)
- Once the supplier is finalized, you issue a Purchase Order.
- This is the official confirmation that you‚Äôre buying items from that supplier.
- The supplier will now start preparing to deliver the goods.
‚Üí You confirm the order with the selected supplier.
  (Okay, we‚Äôll buy from you.)

ex: You send a PO to HP Dealer for 10 laptops at ‚Çπ50,000 each.



5Ô∏è‚É£ Payment Entry (Advance) (optional)
- Sometimes, suppliers ask for an advance payment before delivery.
- In that case, you can create an Advance Payment Entry linked to the PO.
‚Üí If supplier needs advance payment before delivery.
  (Pay some amount before getting goods.)

ex: You pay 20% advance to HP Dealer before shipping.



6Ô∏è‚É£ Purchase Receipt
- When the goods are delivered, you record a Purchase Receipt.
- It confirms that items have been received and added to stock (Inventory).
- Stock levels are updated automatically.
- actual stock entry (in this phase our stock & accounting gets impact)
‚Üí When items arrive, record that you‚Äôve received them.
  (Goods received and added to stock.)

ex: You receive 10 laptops ‚Üí Stock increases by 10 units.



7Ô∏è‚É£ Quality Inspection (optional)
- If your company has a quality process, you can inspect items before final acceptance.
- The result (Pass/Fail) is recorded here.
‚Üí Check product quality if required.
  (Check if items are okay or damaged.)

ex: 2 laptops had screen issues ‚Üí marked as ‚ÄúFailed‚Äù in Quality Inspection.



8Ô∏è‚É£ Purchase Invoice
- Once goods are received and verified, you get a supplier invoice (bill).
- You record this as a Purchase Invoice, which creates a payable entry in Accounts.
‚Üí Supplier sends bill ‚Üí record it here.
  (Record supplier‚Äôs invoice for payment.)
  
ex: Invoice #HP123 ‚Äì ‚Çπ5,00,000 created against the PO.


9Ô∏è‚É£ Payment Entry
- Finally, you create a Payment Entry to mark the invoice as paid.
- It reduces your Accounts Payable and updates your bank balance.
‚Üí Make final payment and close the purchase.
  (Pay supplier and finish the cycle.)

ex: Paid ‚Çπ5,00,000 to HP Dealer ‚Üí Payment Entry marked as ‚ÄúCompleted‚Äù.


-----------------------

Cycle image/Flow 
- on folder, also on my NoteBook

-----------------------

Main chain view  :
Material Request ‚Üí Request for Quotation ‚Üí Supplier Quotation ‚Üí Purchase Order ‚Üí Purchase Receipt ‚Üí Purchase Invoice ‚Üí Payment Entry

-----------------------

User Flow:

Buyer ‚Üí Buyer (internal): Material Request  
Buyer ‚Üí Supplier: Request for Quotation  
Supplier ‚Üí Buyer: Supplier Quotation  
Buyer ‚Üí Supplier: Purchase Order  
Buyer ‚Üí Supplier: Advance Payment (optional)  
Supplier ‚Üí Buyer: Goods Delivery ‚Üí Purchase Receipt  
Buyer ‚Üí Buyer: Quality Inspection (optional)  
Supplier ‚Üí Buyer: Invoice  
Buyer ‚Üí Supplier: Final Payment


Final FLow :

(Internal Need)
Buyer ‚Üí creates ‚Üí Material Request
Buyer ‚Üí sends ‚Üí Request for Quotation ‚Üí to Suppliers
Supplier ‚Üí sends ‚Üí Supplier Quotation ‚Üí to Buyer
Buyer ‚Üí sends ‚Üí Purchase Order ‚Üí to Supplier
Buyer ‚Üí makes (optional) ‚Üí Advance Payment
Supplier ‚Üí delivers ‚Üí Goods
Buyer ‚Üí creates ‚Üí Purchase Receipt
Buyer ‚Üí (optional) ‚Üí does Quality Inspection
Supplier ‚Üí sends ‚Üí Purchase Invoice
Buyer ‚Üí makes ‚Üí Final Payment Entry



