Request for Quotation :

üß© Main Section ‚Äì Details

| Field                       | Simple Meaning                                                     |
| --------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **Series**                  | Auto ID format for RFQ (example: PUR-RFQ-YYYY-0001).               |
| **Date**                    | Date of RFQ creation.                                              |
| **Company Billing Address** | Address from where your company is sending the RFQ.                |
| **Required Date**           | When you need the items (important for supplier to know deadline). |
| **Status**                  | Shows document stage (Draft, Submitted, etc.).                     |



üì¶ Suppliers Table

| Field              | Meaning                                                                |
| ------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Supplier**       | Select suppliers to send the RFQ to.                                   |
| **Contact**        | Contact person for that supplier.                                      |
| **Email Id**       | Supplier‚Äôs email where RFQ will be sent.                               |
| **Send Email (‚úî)** | If checked, ERPNext will send this RFQ automatically to that supplier. |


üìã Items Table

| Field             | Meaning                                     |
| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| **Item Code**     | Item you‚Äôre requesting price for.           |
| **Required Date** | When you need it.                           |
| **Quantity**      | How much you need.                          |
| **UOM**           | Unit of Measure (Nos, Kg, etc.).            |
| **Warehouse**     | Warehouse where items will go after buying. |



‚úâÔ∏è Email Details Section

| Field                   | Meaning                                               |
| ----------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------- |
| **Email Template**      | Choose which email format to use when sending RFQs.   |
| **Preview Email**       | See how your email looks before sending.              |
| **Send Attached Files** | If checked, attachments are sent to the supplier.     |
| **Send Document Print** | If checked, the PDF of RFQ is attached automatically. |




üß© Terms and Conditions Section

| Field                    | Meaning                                                                  |
| ------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **Incoterm**             | International commercial term (like FOB, CIF ‚Äì used for shipping/trade). |
| **Terms**                | Predefined term template.                                                |
| **Terms and Conditions** | Editable area to write conditions like delivery time, payment, etc.      |



üß© Printing Settings Section

| Field             | Meaning                                                                    |
| ----------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Print Heading** | Optional heading for print (e.g., ‚ÄúRequest for Quotation ‚Äì IT Equipment‚Äù). |
| **Letter Head**   | Select which company letterhead to print on.                               |


üß∞ Tools Menu

| Option                        | Meaning                                                                                                                       |
| ----------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Link to Material Requests** | Connects this RFQ to one or more Material Requests. *(Fetch items from them)*                                                 |
| **Get Suppliers**             | Automatically pulls suppliers from existing Supplier records or Supplier Groups. *(Useful to send to many suppliers quickly)* |


ü™Ñ Get Items From Button

| Option                | Meaning                                                                               |
| --------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Material Request**  | Pulls items directly from an existing Material Request.                               |
| **Opportunity**       | Fetches items linked with a sales opportunity (if you‚Äôre buying based on sales lead). |
| **Possible Supplier** | Fetches potential suppliers automatically (based on system setup).                    |




