Supplier Quotation :


üß© TAB 1 ‚Äì Details

| Field                     | Simple Meaning                                                                  |
| ------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Series**                | Auto ID pattern (like PUR-SQTN-YYYY-0001).                                      |
| **Supplier**              | The supplier who gave this quotation.                                           |
| **Status**                | Stage of the document (Draft, Submitted, etc.).                                 |
| **Date**                  | Date on which supplier sent the quotation.                                      |
| **Valid Till**            | Till when this quotation is valid (after this date, prices may change).         |
| **Quotation Number**      | Supplier‚Äôs own quotation number (if any).                                       |
| **Cost Center / Project** | Optional fields if you want to link this purchase with a department or project. |


üß© TAB 2 ‚Äì Address & Contact

| Field                       | Meaning                                             |
| --------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------- |
| **Supplier Address**        | Supplier‚Äôs address.                                 |
| **Contact Person**          | Person from the supplier side you‚Äôre in touch with. |
| **Shipping Address**        | Where items will be delivered.                      |
| **Company Billing Address** | Your company‚Äôs billing address.                     |
| **Place of Supply**         | For GST purposes (used in tax calculation).         |


üß© TAB 3 ‚Äì Currency and Price List

| Field                            | Meaning                                                    |
| -------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Currency**                     | Currency of quotation (like INR, USD, etc.).               |
| **Price List**                   | Default buying price list (example: ‚ÄúStandard Buying‚Äù).    |
| **Ignore Pricing Rule**          | Tick if you don‚Äôt want ERPNext to apply any pricing rules. |
| **Items Table**                  | List of items, their quantity, rate, and amount.           |
| **Total Quantity / Total (INR)** | Auto-calculated totals for the quotation.                  |



üß© TAB 4 ‚Äì Taxes and Charges

| Field                                   | Meaning                                                         |
| --------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Tax Category**                        | Type of tax (e.g., GST, Import, etc.).                          |
| **Shipping Rule**                       | Rule for calculating shipping charges (if any).                 |
| **Incoterm**                            | Trade term like FOB, CIF, etc. (optional).                      |
| **Purchase Taxes and Charges Template** | Select a predefined tax template.                               |
| **Purchase Taxes and Charges (Table)**  | Add rows for specific taxes ‚Äì type, account head, rate, amount. |
| **Taxes and Charges Added / Deducted**  | Totals of tax values.                                           |
| **Total Taxes and Charges**             | Combined total tax applied.                                     |



Taxes and Charges Added :::
This is the total of all extra costs or taxes added on top of your item total.

‚Üí It increases your purchase amount.
‚Üí Calculated from all rows in the Purchase Taxes and Charges table where the tax type adds value (like GST, Freight, Customs, etc.).

| Description                       | Amount      |
| --------------------------------- | ----------- |
| Item Total                        | ‚Çπ1,00,000   |
| CGST @9%                          | ‚Çπ9,000      |
| SGST @9%                          | ‚Çπ9,000      |
| Freight                           | ‚Çπ2,000      |
| **Taxes and Charges Added (INR)** | **‚Çπ20,000** |

----------

Taxes and Charges Deducted :::
This is the total of all taxes or charges subtracted from your total amount.

‚Üí It reduces your purchase amount.
‚Üí Calculated from rows in the Purchase Taxes and Charges table where the tax type deducts value (like TDS, discount, etc.).


| Description                          | Amount      |
| ------------------------------------ | ----------- |
| Item Total                           | ‚Çπ1,00,000   |
| TDS @10%                             | ‚Çπ-10,000    |
| **Taxes and Charges Deducted (INR)** | **‚Çπ10,000** |

----------

Purchase Taxes and Charges (Table)- each field :::
Type 
- The nature of the tax/charge. Common types:
- On Net Total ‚Üí calculated on total amount.
- On Previous Row Amount ‚Üí tax applied on previous tax‚Äôs value.
- Actual ‚Üí fixed value (not percentage).
- On Item Quantity ‚Üí tax per item quantity.


Account Head
The account in your Chart of Accounts where the tax/charge will be posted.
Example: ‚ÄúCGST - Input Tax‚Äù, ‚ÄúFreight Charges‚Äù, ‚ÄúCustom Duty‚Äù.


Tax Rate
The percentage rate of the tax/charge.
Example: 18% for GST.


Amount
Calculated automatically (based on rate and base). You can also manually enter it if Type = Actual.


Total
Auto-calculated total after applying the tax/charge


üß© TAB 5 ‚Äì Additional Discount and Totals

| Field                              | Meaning                                 |
| ---------------------------------- | --------------------------------------- |
| **Apply Additional Discount On**   | Choose base (Net Total or Grand Total). |
| **Additional Discount % / Amount** | Add overall discount.                   |
| **Grand Total**                    | Total amount before rounding.           |
| **Rounded Total**                  | Final rounded amount.                   |
| **Disable Rounded Total**          | Prevent rounding if not needed.         |


Apply Additional Discount On :::
- This dropdown decides on what base the discount will be applied.

| Option          | Meaning                                                                   |
| --------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Net Total**   | Discount is applied on the *total item amount* (before taxes).            |
| **Grand Total** | Discount is applied on the *final amount after adding taxes and charges.* |

-----------------

Additional Discount Percentage :::
- This field is used to give the discount as a percentage.

-----------------

Additional Discount Amount (INR)
- This is for giving a fixed rupee amount discount instead of a percentage.

-----------------


üß© TAB 6 ‚Äì Terms

| Field                    | Meaning                                              |
| ------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| **Terms Template**       | Choose a saved Terms and Conditions template.        |
| **Terms and Conditions** | Type or edit payment terms, delivery, warranty, etc. |


üß© TAB 7 ‚Äì More Info

| Section                                | Fields                                                      | Meaning                                         |
| -------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------- |
| **Printing Settings**                  | Letter Head, Print Heading                                  | Choose letterhead and custom heading for print. |
| **Group Same Items**                   | Combine identical items in print preview.                   |                                                 |
| **Additional Info ‚Üí Is Subcontracted** | If checked, this quotation is for subcontracting materials. |                                                 |


- Subcontracting in ERPNext means you send your raw materials or components to an external supplier (subcontractor), and they use those materials to manufacture 
  or assemble a finished product for you.
- So, you own the raw materials, but the subcontractor performs the work (like fabrication, coating, assembly, etc.).

- Subcontracting materials are the raw materials or components that you supply to the subcontractor to make the final product.


‚öôÔ∏è Special Checkbox Fields

| Field                 | Meaning                                                                 |
| --------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Is Reverse Charge** | Used for reverse charge tax scenarios (GST-related). Usually unchecked. |

This checkbox is used when you (the buyer) have to pay GST directly to the government instead of your supplier.
Normally, the supplier collects GST and pays it to the government.
But under Reverse Charge Mechanism (RCM) ‚Äî The buyer is responsible for paying GST to the government.


:) Tools Menu

| Option                        | Meaning                                                                           |
| ----------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Link to Material Requests** | Connect this quotation to original Material Requests. *(Useful for traceability)* |



:) Get Items From Button

| Option                    | Meaning                                                |
| ------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------ |
| **Material Request**      | Pull items directly from an existing Material Request. |
| **Request for Quotation** | Pull items from a specific RFQ sent earlier.           |


Accounting Dimensions :

Cost Center
‚Üí What it is: the department/location that will bear the cost.
‚Üí Why use it: to know which department spent money (eg. IT, Production, Sales).
‚Üí Effect: Purchase values get recorded against that cost center for reporting and P&L breakdown.
‚Üí Example: Laptops bought for IT ‚Üí Cost Center = IT Department.

Project
‚Üí What it is: project code/name this purchase belongs to.
‚Üí Why use it: to track expenses against a specific project (billing, margin, budget).
‚Üí Effect: Costs are attributed to the project for cost-to-complete and profitability checks.
‚Üí Example: Laptops for Project Alpha ‚Üí Project = Project Alpha.



:) Totals section

Grand Total - 
The final amount after:
- Adding all item amounts
- Adding all ‚ÄúTaxes and Charges Added‚Äù
- Subtracting ‚ÄúTaxes and Charges Deducted‚Äù(TDS)
- Subtracting ‚ÄúAdditional Discount‚Äù


Rounding Adjustment
- This shows the tiny difference that comes when ERPNext rounds the Grand Total to the nearest whole number.
- It‚Äôs an auto-calculated field ‚Äî you don‚Äôt type anything.


Rounded Total
- This is the final payable amount after rounding.
- It‚Äôs what actually shows on the printed invoice and used for payment.0.000.00

Disable Rounded Total
- If you tick this ‚úÖ checkbox, ERPNext will not round the amount.
- It will keep the exact decimal value from the Grand Total.


üè† Address & Contact Tab
| **Field Name**                 | **Who It Belongs To** | **Simple Meaning / Use**                                                                                                |
| ------------------------------ | --------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| üè¢ **Supplier Address**        | Supplier              | The supplier‚Äôs registered or communication address. Used for correspondence and printed on RFQ / PO / Invoice.          |
| üë§ **Contact Person**          | Supplier              | Name of the person you‚Äôre dealing with from that supplier. Auto-fills phone/email if stored in Supplier Master.         |
| üöö **Shipping Address**        | Buyer (Your Company)  | The location where goods should be **delivered** by the supplier.                                                       |
| üßæ **Company Billing Address** | Buyer (Your Company)  | The **official company address** where the supplier‚Äôs invoice will be billed to. Appears on printed purchase documents. |
| üìç **Place of Supply**         | Buyer (For GST)       | Used to determine **GST applicability** (intra-state or inter-state). Comes from shipping address or manually selected. |


Other:
| Field                       | Meaning                                                                      | Includes Taxes? |
| --------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------- |
| **Total**                   | Sum of all item amounts (qty √ó rate) before any discounts or taxes.          | ‚ùå No            |
| **Net Total**               | Sum of all item amounts **after item-level discounts** but **before taxes**. | ‚ùå No            |
| **Taxes and Charges Total** | Sum of all applied taxes and charges.                                        | ‚Äî               |
| **Grand Total**             | **Net Total + Taxes and Charges Total**                                      | ‚úÖ Yes           |
| **Rounded Total**           | Rounded version of Grand Total (based on rounding settings).                 | ‚úÖ Yes           |



----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Purchase Order 

| **Field / Section**              | **Simple Meaning (Easy to Remember)**                            |
| -------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Series**                       | Auto-generated number format (like PUR-ORD-YYYY-0001).           |
| **Date**                         | Date when PO is created.                                         |
| **Supplier**                     | The supplier you‚Äôre buying from.                                 |
| **Required By**                  | When you need the items ready.                                   |
| **Expected Delivery**            | Date supplier should deliver goods.                              |
| **Apply Tax Withholding Amount** | Used for TDS (Tax Deducted at Source).                           |
| **Is Reverse Charge**            | Buyer pays GST directly to govt (not supplier).                  |
| **Is Subcontracted**             | Tick if you‚Äôre sending raw materials to a supplier for job work. |


‚ÄúApply Tax Withholding Amount‚Äù :
- In ERPNext, the ‚ÄúApply Tax Withholding Amount‚Äù option is used to automatically deduct Tax Deducted at Source (TDS) or Withholding Tax from a transaction
 (like a Purchase Invoice, Payment Entry, or Journal Entry) based on predefined rules.


üßæ What is Tax Withholding?
Tax Withholding (TDS) means that when you pay a supplier (or sometimes receive money from a customer), you deduct a percentage of the amount as tax and pay that to the government instead of paying the full amount to the other party.


Example (India context):
- You pay ‚Çπ100,000 to a consultant.
- TDS @10% is applicable.
- You pay ‚Çπ90,000 to the consultant and ‚Çπ10,000 to the government.
ERPNext should automatically calculate and show that ‚Çπ10,000 was withheld.

	
üßÆ Effect on Accounting
- Expense (or income) is recorded in full.
- A liability (TDS Payable) is created for the withheld amount.
- Net payable/receivable is reduced by the TDS amount.



