----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


Item

| **Section / Field**                | **Simple Meaning (Easy to Remember)**                |
| ---------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| **Item Code / Item Name**          | Unique ID and name for the item.                     |
| **Item Group**                     | Category of item (e.g., Raw Material, Product).      |
| **HSN/SAC**                        | GST classification code for goods/services.          |
| **Default Unit of Measure (UOM)**  | Base unit (e.g., Nos, Kg, Box).                      |
| **Disabled**                       | Stops item from being used in transactions.          |
| **Allow Alternative Item**         | Allows linking substitute item.                      |
| **Maintain Stock**                 | Tick if stock is tracked in inventory.               |
| **Has Variants**                   | Tick if item has variations (like color/size).       |
| **Opening Stock / Valuation Rate** | Initial quantity and rate while creation.            |
| **Standard Selling Rate**          | Default selling price.                               |
| **Is Fixed Asset**                 | Tick if item is a company asset (not regular stock). |

here,

Allow Alternative Item :
- If ‚úÖ checked, ERPNext allows this item to be replaced with another equivalent item in transactions.
- Useful when the exact item is unavailable, and you want to use a substitute item instead

- Sometimes the main item is out of stock, discontinued, or temporarily unavailable. Instead of blocking the order, ERPNext can suggest or allow an alternative item 
 (defined under the same item or linked through ‚ÄúItem Alternative‚Äù Doctype).

How works

| **Step** | **What Happens**                                                                                                           |
| -------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| 1Ô∏è‚É£      | You tick **Allow Alternative Item** in Item master.                                                                        |
| 2Ô∏è‚É£      | You link related items under **Item Alternative** Doctype.                                                                 |
| 3Ô∏è‚É£      | When that item is used in an order and stock is not available, ERPNext suggests available alternative items automatically. |

-------

Maintain Stock:
- If ‚úÖ checked, ERPNext will track stock quantity and value for this item. If ‚ùå unchecked, ERPNext treats it as a non-stock item.

| **Situation**                           | **Maintain Stock?** |
| --------------------------------------- | ------------------- |
| Raw Material / Finished Goods           | ‚úÖ Yes               |
| Consumables (tracked inventory)         | ‚úÖ Yes               |
| Labor / Service / Subcontract Charges   | ‚ùå No                |
| Office Expenses (like Stationery, Rent) | ‚ùå No                |

Maintain Stock = tells ERPNext whether to track inventory movement for that item or treat it as a non-stock (service/expense) item.

-------

HSN and SAC are classification codes used in GST (Goods and Services Tax) systems ‚Äî primarily in India, but ERPNext supports them globally for tax compliance.

| Code Type | Full Form                         | Applies To           | Purpose                                                 |
| --------- | --------------------------------- | -------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------- |
| **HSN**   | Harmonized System of Nomenclature | **Goods / Products** | Used to classify goods for GST and international trade. |
| **SAC**   | Services Accounting Code          | **Services**         | Used to classify services for GST and taxation.         |

-------

A Fixed Asset in ERPNext (and in accounting generally) is:
- If ‚úÖ checked, ERPNext treats this item as a Fixed Asset instead of inventory.
- A tangible or intangible item that your company owns, uses for operations, and expects to use for more than one accounting period.

Examples:
- Computers, furniture, vehicles, machinery ‚Äî tangible assets
- Patents, software licenses ‚Äî intangible assets

This tells ERPNext that the item you are buying is not meant for resale or consumption, but is a company asset ‚Äî like furniture, computers, machinery, etc.

- So instead of tracking it as stock, ERPNext will create an Asset record after you buy it.



