| --------------- | ----------------------------------- |
| **Description** | Item details shown on transactions. |
| **Brand**       | Brand name of item.                 |


üìè Units of Measure (UOMs)

| Field                 | Meaning                                       |
| --------------------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| **UOM Table**         | Define alternate UOMs (e.g., 1 Box = 10 Nos). |
| **Conversion Factor** | Defines relation between UOMs.                |

here,
- In ERPNext, Conversion Factor defines the relationship between two Units of Measurement (UOMs) for the same Item.
- It tells ERPNext how many base units are contained in one alternate UOM.

| Item   | Base UOM | Alternate UOM | Conversion Factor | Meaning            |
| ------ | -------- | ------------- | ----------------- | ------------------ |
| Cement | Kg       | Bag           | 50                | 1 Bag = 50 Kg      |
| Paper  | Nos      | Box           | 10                | 1 Box = 10 Nos     |
| Cable  | Meter    | Roll          | 100               | 1 Roll = 100 Meter |



