üí∞ Taxes

| Field                                  | Meaning                                  |
| -------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------- |
| **Is Ineligible for Input Tax Credit** | No GST credit allowed for this item.     |
| **Item Tax Table**                     | Define tax template, rate, and category. |

Input Tax Credit (ITC) in GST?
Input Tax Credit (ITC) means you can claim credit for the GST you paid on purchases (inputs, goods, or services) that are used in your business.

For example:
- You buy goods worth ‚Çπ10,000 + 18% GST = ‚Çπ1,800
- You can claim ‚Çπ1,800 as input tax credit, reducing your GST payable on sales.

Ineligible for Input Tax Credit‚Äù Mean?
- Some purchases are not allowed to be claimed as input tax credit under GST rules.
- If a purchase is ineligible, you cannot use that GST amount to offset your output tax liability.

- means if ITC applied then when you buy something then you pay GST( e.g. 1800 rs.), after that when you sell that product you get that GST from your buyer, so now you get 1800 
  so here only one person pay GST to gevernment.( if you sell then you get your paid gst then it consider your buyer pays gst)

- but if you ineligible for that so you only pays GST after that when you sell you not get any GST for your recovery ....
  
| Type of Expense                         | ITC Allowed? | Reason                   |
| --------------------------------------- | ------------ | ------------------------ |
| Personal use expenses                   | ‚ùå No         | Not for business purpose |
| Motor vehicles (except certain cases)   | ‚ùå No         | Restricted ITC           |
| Food, beverages, club memberships       | ‚ùå No         | Personal nature          |
| Goods/services used for exempt supplies | ‚ùå No         | Not taxable              |
| Purchase for non-business use           | ‚ùå No         | Not related to business  |


