----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Buying Settings


üè∑Ô∏è 1. Naming Series and Price Defaults

| **Field**                                                               | **Simple Meaning (Easy to Remember)**                                                                        |
| ----------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **Supplier Naming By**                                                  | How supplier records will be named (by *Supplier Name* or *Naming Series*).                                  |
| **Default Supplier Group**                                              | Default group assigned when new supplier is created.                                                         |
| **Default Buying Price List**                                           | Default price list for all purchase-related transactions.                                                    |
| **Action If Same Rate Is Not Maintained**                               | What to do if rate differs between Purchase Order, Receipt, and Invoice ‚Äî options: *Stop*, *Warn*, *Ignore*. |
| **Role Allowed to Override Stop Action**                                | Role that can override the "Stop" action if rates differ.                                                    |
| **Is Purchase Order Required for Purchase Invoice & Receipt Creation?** | Enforces linking Purchase Orders before Purchase Receipt/Invoice creation.                                   |
| **Is Purchase Receipt Required for Purchase Invoice Creation?**         | Enforces linking Purchase Receipt before Purchase Invoice creation.                                          |
| **Blanket Order Allowance (%)**                                         | How much quantity (%) can exceed from Blanket Order limit.                                                   |
| **Update Frequency of Project**                                         | Defines how often total purchase cost should update in related Project ‚Äî e.g., *Each Transaction*.           |



üì¶ 2. Transaction Settings

| **Field**                                                  | **Meaning**                                                                    |
| ---------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **Allow Supplier Quotation with Zero Quantity**            | Allows submitting quotations without specifying quantity (for rate contracts). |
| **Allow Request for Quotation with Zero Quantity**         | Allows creating RFQs without quantity.                                         |
| **Use Transaction Date Exchange Rate**                     | Uses the exchange rate of the transaction date (not from Purchase Order).      |
| **Maintain Same Rate Throughout the Purchase Cycle**       | Ensures same item rate is maintained across PO ‚Üí PR ‚Üí PI.                      |
| **Allow Item to Be Added Multiple Times in a Transaction** | Enables adding same item multiple times in the same document.                  |
| **Bill for Rejected Quantity in Purchase Invoice**         | Bills even for rejected quantities (if enabled).                               |
| **Set Valuation Rate for Rejected Materials**              | Automatically create accounting entries for rejected materials.                |
| **Disable Last Purchase Rate**                             | Hides the ‚ÄúLast Purchase Rate‚Äù suggestion in forms.                            |
| **Allow Purchase Order with Zero Quantity**                | Allows PO creation without specific quantities ‚Äî used for rate contracts.      |


here,

Use Transaction Date Exchange Rate:
- While making Purchase Invoice from Purchase Order, use Exchange Rate on Invoice's transaction date rather than inheriting it from Purchase Order. Only applies for Purchase Invoice.

Bill for Rejected Quantity in Purchase Invoice:
- if checked, Rejected Quantity will be included while making Purchase Invoice from Purchase Receipt.


üèóÔ∏è 3. Subcontracting Settings

| **Field**                                           | **Meaning**                                                                     |
| --------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Backflush Raw Materials of Subcontract Based On** | Defines how raw materials are consumed ‚Äî usually *BOM (Bill of Materials)*.     |
| **Over Transfer Allowance (%)**                     | % of extra raw materials allowed to send to subcontractor.                      |
| **Auto Create Subcontracting Order**                | Automatically create Subcontracting Order when Purchase Order is submitted.     |
| **Auto Create Purchase Receipt**                    | Automatically create Purchase Receipt when Subcontracting Receipt is submitted. |



üìß 4. Request for Quotation (RFQ)

| **Field**                        | **Meaning**                                                                                                  |
| -------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **Fixed Outgoing Email Account** | Specify a fixed email account for sending RFQs ‚Äî avoids using user‚Äôs personal email or global outgoing mail. |






XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX


REPORTS IN INSHORT

üèÜ Key Reports

| **Report Name**                   | **Simple Meaning / Use**                                                                                        |
| --------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Purchase Analytics**            | Summary of all purchase transactions ‚Äî analyze total spending by item, supplier, or date.                       |
| **Purchase Order Analysis**       | Compare **Ordered vs Received vs Billed** quantities and values for every Purchase Order.                       |
| **Supplier-Wise Sales Analytics** | Shows how much business (buying & selling) is done with each supplier ‚Äî good for supplier performance tracking. |
| **Items to Order and Receive**    | Lists all items that need to be **ordered or received**, based on stock levels and pending POs.                 |
| **Purchase Order Trends**         | Visual report showing **monthly or yearly purchase patterns** ‚Äî helps identify demand trends.                   |
| **Procurement Tracker**           | Tracks full procurement flow from **Material Request ‚Üí RFQ ‚Üí Purchase Order ‚Üí Receipt ‚Üí Invoice**.              |


üì¶ Other Reports

| **Report Name**                                            | **Simple Meaning / Use**                                                                   |
| ---------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **Items To Be Requested**                                  | Shows items that should be requested soon (usually below reorder level).                   |
| **Item-wise Purchase History**                             | Displays purchase rate and quantity history per item ‚Äî helps in pricing decisions.         |
| **Purchase Receipt Trends**                                | Trend report showing how many items were received over time.                               |
| **Purchase Invoice Trends**                                | Tracks number/value of invoices created ‚Äî helps monitor billing trends.                    |
| **Subcontracted Raw Materials To Be Transferred**          | Lists raw materials that must be sent to subcontractors for manufacturing.                 |
| **Subcontracted Item To Be Received**                      | Shows subcontracted finished goods pending receipt from supplier.                          |
| **Supplier Quotation Comparison**                          | Compare multiple supplier quotations side by side to choose the best offer.                |
| **Material Requests for which Supplier Quotation Created** | Tracks which material requests already have quotations linked ‚Äî avoids duplicate RFQs.     |
| **Supplier Addresses And Contacts**                        | Combined list of all supplier addresses and contacts ‚Äî for communication and verification. |



































































































































